.TH BUNPY 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy \- one binary for Python: runtime, packages, bundler, tests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy
.I file.py
[\fIargs...\fR]
.br
.B bunpy
.I command
[\fIargs\fR]
.br
.B bunpy
\-\-version
.br
.B bunpy
\-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bunpy
is one static Go binary that runs Python scripts, lists embedded
stdlib modules, and prints build metadata. Subcommands land per
the per-version ladder in
.IR docs/ROADMAP.md .
The runtime piece pipes source through gopapy (parser),
gocopy (compiler), and goipy (bytecode VM); none of those need
to be installed separately.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B run
Run a Python script. See
.BR bunpy-run (1).
.TP
.B stdlib
List the Python stdlib modules embedded in the binary. See
.BR bunpy-stdlib (1).
.TP
.B version
Print version, commit, build date, and pinned toolchain commits.
See
.BR bunpy-version (1).
.TP
.B help
Print long-form help for a subcommand. See
.BR bunpy-help (1).
.TP
.B man
Print or install the bundled manpages. See
.BR bunpy-man (1).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BUNPY_INSTALL_DIR
Used by
.IR install.sh ;
default
.IR $HOME/.bunpy .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $HOME/.bunpy/bin/bunpy
Default install path.
.TP
.I $HOME/.bunpy/share/man
Default man-install destination.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy-run (1),
.BR bunpy-stdlib (1),
.BR bunpy-version (1),
.BR bunpy-help (1),
.BR bunpy-man (1).
.PP
Project page: <https://github.com/tamnd/bunpy>.
